        "Do not assert that any group is or is not eligible for REAL ID in a given state. REAL ID rules involve both federal minimums and state implementation that may change. Use 'verify' and 'may vary' language only.": "請勿斷言任何族群在特定州是否符合 REAL ID 資格。REAL ID 規則涉及聯邦最低標準及各州實施方式,且可能變動。請僅使用「核實」與「可能不同」的措辭。",
        "Do not assert that any specific state always uses a shortened renewal cycle for a given visa category. Frame as items to verify with the destination-state DMV. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿斷言特定州在特定簽證類別下一律採用較短的更新週期。請將所有事項表述為需要向目的地州 DMV 核實的項目。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not assert that any visa category is or is not eligible for REAL ID in a given state. REAL ID involves both federal minimums and state implementation that may change. Use 'verify' and 'may vary' language only and follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿斷言任何簽證類別在特定州是否符合 REAL ID 資格。REAL ID 涉及聯邦最低標準及各州實施方式,且可能變動。請僅使用「核實」與「可能不同」的措辭,並遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not assume": "請勿假設",
        "Do not assume a USPS or DMV address update satisfies the federal AR-11 step": "請勿假設 USPS 或 DMV 地址更新可滿足聯邦 AR-11 步驟",
        "Do not assume regulated items follow the same rules across state lines": "請勿假設受規範物品在不同州之間遵循相同規則",
        "Do not assume rules from your origin state apply. Rules vary across state, local, and federal jurisdictions. Verify directly with official sources.": "請勿假設出發州的規則同樣適用。州、地方及聯邦司法管轄區的規則不同。請直接向官方資料來源核實。",
        "Do not characterize voter registration by non-citizens using legal-conclusion or accusatory language. Use neutral framing such as 'generally not eligible' and 'may create immigration complications'. Direct readers to consult a licensed immigration attorney. Do not give procedural advice for any specific state.": "請勿以法律結論或指控性措辭描述非美籍人士的選民登記。請使用中性表述,如「一般沒有資格」與「可能造成移民方面的複雜情況」。請引導讀者諮詢持證移民律師。請勿針對任何特定州提供程序建議。",
        "Do not characterize whether any visa category can establish residency in a specific state as a determination. Frame as classification rules to verify with the school registrar and the state higher-education agency. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿就任何簽證類別在特定州能否建立居住身分作出判定。請以「向學校註冊組及州高等教育機構核實的身分認定規則」表述。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not determine residency. List factors to verify. Direct to the relevant agency or school.": "請勿認定居住身分。列出需核實的因素。請引導至相關機構或學校。",
        "Do not determine that a household 'is' or 'is not' eligible for Medicaid. Frame as items to verify with the state Medicaid agency. Use 'may apply' and 'rules differ by jurisdiction'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿判定家庭「具備」或「不具備」Medicaid 資格。請將所有事項表述為需要向州 Medicaid 機構核實的項目。請使用「可能適用」及「各司法管轄區的規則不同」。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not list which states grant in-state tuition for DACA recipients. Frame as classification rules to verify with the school registrar and the state higher-education agency.": "請勿列出哪些州會核予 DACA 受益人州內學費。請以「向學校註冊組及州高等教育機構核實的身分認定規則」表述。",
        "Do not provide a public-charge determination or say that using benefits 'will' or 'will not' affect immigration. Frame as 'may interact' and recommend consulting a licensed immigration attorney. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿作出公共負擔認定,或陳述使用福利「將」或「不會」影響移民。請以「可能互動」表述,並建議諮詢持證移民律師。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not provide medical or transport instructions for controlled substances.": "請勿提供管制藥物的醫療或運輸指示。",
        "Do not provide tactical instructions for transporting, possessing, hiding, storing, modifying, or avoiding enforcement for regulated items.": "請勿提供運輸、持有、隱藏、儲存、改裝,或規避受規範物品執法的具體操作指示。",
        "Do not provide tax advice. Direct to official tax agency and qualified professionals.": "請勿提供稅務建議。請引導至官方稅務機構及合格專業人員。",
        "Do not provide tax advice. Direct to state tax agency or qualified tax professional.": "請勿提供稅務建議。請引導至州稅機構或合格稅務專業人員。",
        "Do not say a Board of Nursing in a particular state grants or refuses an applicant's NCLEX path. Use 'verify with the destination Board of Nursing'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述特定州的護理委員會是否核准或拒絕申請人的 NCLEX 路徑。請使用「向目的地護理委員會核實」的措辭。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not say a particular aid program 'is open to' or 'is closed to' DACA recipients or LPRs. Use 'verify with the state aid agency and the school financial-aid office'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述特定助學金計劃「對 DACA 受益人或 LPR 開放」或「不開放」。請使用「向州助學金機構及學校助學金辦公室核實」的措辭。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not say a person 'can' or 'cannot' enroll. Use 'verify current eligibility categories with the marketplace operator' since federal rules have changed. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述某人「可」或「不可」投保。由於聯邦規則已有變動,請使用「向保險市集營運方核實目前的資格類別」。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not state how a specific state defines residency for a given visa category or that someone 'is' a resident. Frame as 'rules differ by jurisdiction' and 'verify with the destination-state tax agency'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述特定州對特定簽證類別如何認定居住身分,或某人「是」居民。請以「各司法管轄區的規則不同」及「向目的地州稅務機構核實」表述。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not state how a specific state defines residency or that someone 'is' a resident. Frame as 'rules differ by jurisdiction' and 'verify with the destination-state tax agency'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述特定州如何認定居住身分,或某人「是」居民。請以「各司法管轄區的規則不同」及「向目的地州稅務機構核實」表述。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not state that any specific board does or does not license a given visa category. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state board. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述特定委員會是否會核發執照給特定簽證類別。請將所有事項表述為需要向目的地州委員會核實的項目。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not state that any specific board does or does not license non-citizens. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state board. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述特定委員會是否會核發執照給非美籍人士。請將所有事項表述為需要向目的地州委員會核實的項目。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not state that any specific person is or is not required to register. Frame as a federal requirement that 'may apply' depending on age and sex, with state implementation details to verify. Use neutral language and follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述任何特定人士是否須登記。請以「可能適用」表述為依年齡與性別而定的聯邦要求,並列出需要核實的州實施細節。請使用中性措辭,並遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Do not state whether the user is eligible for licensure. Only identify requirements to verify.": "請勿陳述使用者是否符合執照資格。僅列出需核實的要求事項。",
        "Do not state which states do or do not issue licenses to a given group, and do not list specific accepted documents. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state DMV.": "請勿陳述哪些州會或不會核發駕照給特定族群,亦勿列出特定可接受的文件。請將所有事項表述為需要向目的地州 DMV 核實的項目。",
        "Do not state which states issue or do not issue licenses to a given visa category, and do not list specific accepted documents. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state DMV. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "請勿陳述哪些州會或不會核發駕照給特定簽證類別,亦勿列出特定可接受的文件。請將所有事項表述為需要向目的地州 DMV 核實的項目。請遵循 SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Document lists accepted by state DMVs for non-citizen license or state-ID applicants can differ from those accepted for U.S. citizens, and accepted combinations may vary by jurisdiction.": "各州 DMV 對非美籍駕照或州身分證申請人接受的文件清單,可能與美國公民適用的清單不同;接受的文件組合也可能因司法管轄區而異。",
        "Documents for proof of identity": "身分證明文件",
        "Done": "完成",
        "Driver's license": "駕照",
        "Driving across one or more state lines for travel.": "為旅遊而駕車穿越一個或多個州界。",
        "Driving with coverage that does not meet destination-state minimums can create compliance and financial problems.": "以未達目的地州最低承保範圍的保險駕駛,可能造成法規遵循與財務問題。",
        "Drug screen requirements": "藥物檢測要求",
        "Edit selections": "編輯選項",
        "Emissions testing requirement": "排放檢測要求",
        "Employer policy": "雇主政策",
        "Employment Authorization": "工作許可",
        "Employment paperwork": "就業文件",
        "Endorsement requirements if already licensed": "若已持有執照,背書認可的要求",
        "Endorsement, reciprocity, temporary permits, and continuing education requirements vary by state and profession.": "背書認可、互惠協議、臨時許可,以及繼續教育要求,各州及各專業領域不同。",
        "Endorsement, reciprocity, temporary practice, and continuing education.": "背書認可、互惠協議、臨時執業,以及繼續教育要求。",
        "Enhanced or REAL ID": "Enhanced 或 REAL ID",
        "Establishing a new permanent residence in the destination state.": "在目的地州建立新的長期住所。",
        "Eviction and late-fee rules": "驅逐及逾期費規則",
        "Example checklist categories": "範例清單類別",
        "Exploring options. Receive a broad overview checklist.": "正在評估選項。取得一份涵蓋廣泛主題的清單。",
        "F-1 OPT and STEM OPT specific. Use verify with the DSO and SEVP Portal guidance. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing and penalty-avoidance phrasing). Do not advise on a specific status outcome.": "F-1 OPT 及 STEM OPT 專屬。請使用「向 DSO 及 SEVP Portal 指引核實」的措辭。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單(法律結論式措辭及與規避罰則相關的措辭)。請勿就特定身分結果提供建議。",
        "F-1 specific. Frame as verify with both DSOs and reference Study in the States or ICE materials. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "F-1 專屬。請以「向雙方 DSO 核實」並參考 Study in the States 或 ICE 資料的方式表述。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "F-1 students on post-completion OPT or a STEM OPT extension generally use the SEVP Portal or work with their DSO to update physical and mailing address, employer information, and other personal data, typically within 10 days of a change. Unemployment-day limits during OPT continue to apply during and after a move.": "F-1 學生在完成課程後 OPT 或 STEM OPT 延伸期間,一般透過 SEVP Portal 或與其 DSO 合作更新實際與郵寄地址、雇主資訊及其他個人資料,通常於變更後 10 天內辦理。OPT 期間的失業日上限規定在搬家期間及之後仍持續適用。",
        "F-1, J-1, M-1, and Q specific. Frame as items to verify with IRS guidance and the employer. Do not state that a particular worker is exempt from FICA. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "F-1、J-1、M-1 及 Q 類專屬。請將所有事項表述為需向 IRS 指引及雇主核實的項目。請勿陳述特定工作者豁免 FICA。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Factors that may affect residency for tuition, taxes, licensing, benefits.": "可能影響學費、稅務、執照及福利相關居住身分認定的因素。",
        "Failing to register on time may affect eligibility for federal benefits, federal jobs, and naturalization later, even though the requirement is federal. State DMV workflows can also trigger automatic registration, which applicants should understand before applying.": "雖然此規定為聯邦規定,未依時登記可能日後影響聯邦福利、聯邦職位及歸化資格。州 DMV 的流程也可能觸發自動登記,申請人在申辦前應先了解。",
        "Family move": "家庭搬遷",
        "Federal HealthCare.gov guidance describes a list of immigration statuses considered lawfully present for purposes of the Affordable Care Act marketplace, which includes many common nonimmigrant categories. These categories can purchase coverage without a five-year waiting period that applies in many Medicaid contexts.": "聯邦 HealthCare.gov 指引列出了《平價醫療法案》保險市集視為合法居留的移民身分類別,涵蓋許多常見的非移民類別。這些類別可購買保險,且不適用許多 Medicaid 情境下的五年等待期。",
        "Federal Medicaid and CHIP rules generally include a five-year waiting period for many qualified non-citizens after obtaining qualified status, with several federal exceptions. States may use an option that removes the waiting period for children and pregnant people, and some states cover certain groups with state funds.": "聯邦 Medicaid 及 CHIP 規則一般包含許多合格非美籍人士在取得合格身分後須滿五年等待期的規定,並有若干聯邦例外。各州可選擇取消兒童及孕婦的等待期,部分州則以州經費承保特定族群。",
        "Federal Medicare guidance generally describes eligibility for non-citizens who are lawfully admitted for permanent residence and have lived in the United States for five continuous years. Federal Medicaid rules for most nonimmigrants are narrower than for LPRs, with state-specific options for emergency Medicaid and for lawfully residing children and pregnant individuals.": "聯邦 Medicare 指引一般說明,合法取得永久居留並在美國連續居住滿五年的非美籍人士具備資格。聯邦 Medicaid 規則對多數非移民人士的範圍比對 LPR 更窄,並有針對緊急 Medicaid 及合法居留之兒童與懷孕個人的州別選項。",
        "Federal REAL ID rules require evidence of lawful status, and many states issue a REAL ID to nonimmigrant visa holders only with an expiration date that does not extend past the I-94, the visa, or another underlying federal document. Implementation differs between states, and standard (non-REAL-ID) options may or may not be offered.": "聯邦 REAL ID 規則要求合法身分證明;許多州核發給非移民簽證持有人的 REAL ID,其有效期不會超出 I-94、簽證或其他所依據的聯邦文件。各州實施方式不同,是否提供標準(非 REAL ID)選項也不一致。",
        "Federal SNAP, TANF, and similar programs apply a waiting period to many qualified non-citizens. Some states use state funds to operate replacement or supplemental programs that cover groups not eligible for the federal program, with differing rules.": "聯邦 SNAP、TANF 及類似計劃對許多合格非美籍人士設有等待期。部分州以州經費營運替代或補充計劃,涵蓋不符合聯邦計劃資格的族群,規則各有不同。",
        "Federal law": "聯邦法",
        "Federal law (INA section 265) generally directs non-citizens to report a change of address to USCIS within 10 days of moving, typically through Form AR-11 or the USCIS online change-of-address tool. The federal filing is separate from updating a state DMV record, an employer, a school, or the U.S. Postal Service.": "聯邦法(INA 第 265 條)一般要求非美籍人士在搬家後 10 天內向 USCIS 通報地址變更,通常透過 AR-11 表格或 USCIS 線上地址變更工具辦理。此聯邦通報與更新州 DMV 紀錄、雇主、學校或美國郵政機關屬不同步驟。",
        "Federal law generally requires motor vehicle offices to offer voter registration to applicants, and forms are screened for citizenship attestations. Non-citizens generally are not eligible to register for federal elections, and a registration record can later create immigration complications.": "聯邦法一般要求車輛管理機關向申請人提供選民登記服務,並對表格進行公民身分確認的審核。非美籍人士一般沒有資格登記參加聯邦選舉,登記紀錄日後可能造成移民方面的複雜情況。",
        "Federal residency for tax purposes determines whether worldwide income is reported, which IRS forms apply, and how an interstate move's first and last year are filed at the federal level, separately from state residency rules.": "聯邦稅務居住身分決定是否需申報全球收入、適用哪些 IRS 表格,以及跨州搬遷在聯邦層級首尾年度的申報方式,與州居住身分規則屬不同層次。",
        "Federal rules govern which immigration statuses can purchase coverage and receive financial help through the Affordable Care Act marketplace, and those rules have changed. State-based marketplaces and state-funded programs add another layer that can differ between origin and destination.": "聯邦規則規範哪些移民身分可透過《平價醫療法案》(ACA)保險市集購買保險及取得財務協助,且該規則已有變動。州自營保險市集及州經費計劃則增加了一層在出發州與目的地州之間可能不同的規範。",
        "Federal tax authority": "聯邦稅務機關",
        "Federal tax authority general guidance": "聯邦稅務機關一般指引",
        "Filing Requirements, Residency, and Telecommuting FAQs": "申報要求、居住身分及遠距工作常見問題",
        "Flags risk levels so you know where to focus": "標示風險等級,協助您找出重點",
        "Florida Board of Governors page on residency for tuition purposes for the State University System. flbog.edu returns 403 to non-browser requests (Cloudflare); this is a known false negative.": "Florida Board of Governors 關於州立大學系統學費目的居住身分的頁面。flbog.edu 對非瀏覽器請求回傳 403(Cloudflare);屬已知的假陰性。",
        "Florida FLHSMV documentation page for nonimmigrant applicants for driver licenses and identification cards.": "Florida FLHSMV 對非移民駕照及身分證申請人的文件頁面。",
        "Follow device language": "依裝置語言",
        "For L-1, whether the new worksite is the same qualifying U.S. office described in the petition or a different one": "對 L-1 而言,新工作地點是否為申請書描述的同一符合資格的美國辦公地點",
        "For L-1A, L-1B, and O-1 status, USCIS treats a move to a new worksite as a material change in some fact patterns and not others, depending on what the original petition described and whether the new location is consistent with the approved terms. The analysis follows the underlying petition, not LCA-based MSA rules.": "對於 L-1A、L-1B 及 O-1 身分,USCIS 是否將工作地點變更視為重大變更,因情況而異,取決於原申請書描述及新地點是否符合已核准的條款。評估依據為原申請書,而非以 LCA 為基礎的 MSA 規則。",
        "For O-1, whether the new venue, event, engagement, or agent arrangement falls within the approved petition scope": "對 O-1 而言,新場地、活動、合作或經紀安排是否落在已核准申請的範圍內",
        "For federal tax purposes, a non-citizen is generally treated as a resident alien if they meet the Substantial Presence Test or hold lawful permanent resident status, with separate rules in IRS Publication 519 for exempt individuals (such as certain F-1, J-1, M-1, and Q students and scholars) whose days of presence may not count.": "就聯邦稅而言,非美籍人士若通過實質居留測試或持有合法永久居民身分,一般被視為稅務居民外國人;IRS Publication 519 對豁免個人(例如某些 F-1、J-1、M-1 及 Q 類學生與學者)另有規定,其居留天數可能不計入。",
        "For nursing specifically, how the destination state treats primary state of residency under the Nurse Licensure Compact for a non-citizen who declares either the country of origin or the compact state, and any credentials-evaluation requirement (for example, CGFNS) for internationally educated applicants": "就護理而言,當非美籍人士宣告原國籍或互認協議州為主要居住州時,目的地州在護士執照互認協議下如何處理;以及對受國際教育申請人的學歷評估要求(例如 CGFNS)",
        "Form AR-11 paper version posted on uscis.gov.": "張貼於 uscis.gov 上的 AR-11 紙本版本。",
        "Frame AR-11 as a federal reporting step to verify, not a guarantee of status. Do not state that any specific status category is or is not covered without source. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing such as the i-word, the p-words, and penalty-avoidance phrasing). Direct readers to consult a licensed immigration attorney for status-specific guidance.": "請將 AR-11 表述為需核實的聯邦通報步驟,而非對身分作出擔保。在缺乏資料來源時,請勿陳述任何特定身分類別是否涵蓋其中。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單(法律結論式措辭,以及與規避罰則相關的措辭)。請引導讀者諮詢持證移民律師以取得特定身分的指引。",
        "Frame as a federal requirement that may apply, with a nonimmigrant exception that may apply based on continuous valid status. Do not state that any specific person is or is not required to register. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "請以「可能適用的聯邦要求,並有可能依持續有效身分而適用的非移民例外」表述。請勿陳述任何特定人士是否須登記。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Frame as items to verify in IRS Publication 519 and with a qualified tax preparer. Do not state a person is a dual-status filer for a particular year. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "請將所有事項表述為需向 IRS Publication 519 及合格稅務代理人核實的項目。請勿陳述某人在特定年度為雙重身分申報人。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Frame as items to verify with CMS and the destination-state Medicaid agency. Federal rules have changed and may continue to change. Do not state a person is or is not eligible. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "請將所有事項表述為需向 CMS 及目的地州 Medicaid 機構核實的項目。聯邦規則已有變動,並可能持續變動。請勿陳述某人是否符合資格。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Frame as items to verify with IRS Publication 519 and a tax preparer. Do not state a person is or is not a resident alien for federal tax purposes. Use may apply and rules differ by jurisdiction. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "請將所有事項表述為需向 IRS Publication 519 及稅務代理人核實的項目。請勿陳述某人就聯邦稅而言是否為稅務居民外國人。請使用「可能適用」及「各司法管轄區的規則不同」。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Frame as items to verify with the DSO or J-1 sponsor and Study in the States or ICE guidance. This item is specific to F-1, M-1, and J-1 status. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing and penalty-avoidance phrasing).": "請將所有事項表述為需向 DSO 或 J-1 贊助方,以及 Study in the States 或 ICE 指引核實的項目。本項目專屬於 F-1、M-1 及 J-1 身分。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單(法律結論式措辭及與規避罰則相關的措辭)。",
        "Frame as items to verify with the current HealthCare.gov or state-based marketplace lists. Do not state any specific category is or is not on the lawfully present list, since federal rules have changed. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "請將所有事項表述為需向目前的 HealthCare.gov 或州自營保險市集清單核實的項目。由於聯邦規則已有變動,請勿陳述任何特定類別是否在合法居留清單中。請避免使用 iOS SafeCopy 應避免清單。",
        "Full disclaimer:": "完整免責聲明:",
