        "IRS guidance generally describes an exemption from FICA tax for wages paid for services performed by F-1, J-1, M-1, and Q nonresident-alien students, scholars, teachers, researchers, and trainees, when the work is part of the activity for which they were admitted and they remain nonresident aliens for federal tax purposes.": "IRS 指引一般說明,F-1、J-1、M-1 及 Q 類非稅務居民外國人之學生、學者、教師、研究人員及受訓人員,因從事其入境目的相關活動所獲得的工資,且其仍為聯邦稅務上的非居民外國人時,可豁免 FICA 稅。",
